d our horizons.</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-large wp-image-492\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/clients_gear-1024x464.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"238\" />Working with Moffitt International is working with intent. We at Moffitt understand the value of time, yours and ours. We will strive to insure that your experience with us will be the most pleasant and rewarding experience that you have had with an executive search and management consulting firm.\r\n\r\nOur consultants are both professional and specialized. Their years of experience coupled with specific industry focus allows them to provide you with the utmost attention and provide you with the potential candidates you need to reach your personal and firm goals.\r\n\r\nThe candidates that we develop on your behalf are typically not active in the marketplace. This allows us proper time for vetting and allows you a reasonable amount of time to ascertain the level of your investment you feel most comfortable. Candidates are a perishable commodity.\r\n<h3>Your Expectations of Us</h3>\r\nYour expectations of our firm include the following at a minimum. (Should you require anything in addition, please communicate those expectations clearly to us when appropriate).\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will treat your search or management consulting needs with the utmost discretion and confidentiality. We will not disclose your identity or specific engagement(s) until the appropriate time, depending on the circumstance.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will respect your time. We will conduct ourselves within very strict industry ethical guidelines and will only present candidates or solutions that we feel are in your best interests. We will NOT make decisions at the (our) practice level that may affect you without your involvement.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will communicate with you often. In the world of unified communications, we will strive to provide you updates across any number of platforms. However, you as the client may select the platform you most desire for that communication.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will protect your interests. As professionals we understand the importance of our relationship. We strive through our process to protect your interests at all times. Your success is the paramount focus of our efforts. Whether your need is short term mission critical or part of a long term strategic plan, the outcome you desire will always be at the forefront of any effort we undertake on your behalf.\r\n<h3>Our Expectations of You</h3>\r\nWithin the scope of your relationship with us, we have certain expectations of you. These expectations strictly have one goal in mind, mutual success. We are sensitive to how you desire to manage our search effort through the assignment\r\n\r\n<span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">A</span>s a business to business consultancy, all of our fees are borne by you the client. Legal and regulatory consideration prevent us from charging or receiving consideration from individuals. We do not undertake any expenses without your specific request or permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"moffitt-body-button\" style=\"color: #445faa;\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?page_id=15\">Get started</a>','Our Clients','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2019-02-01 00:20:47','2019-02-01 00:20:47','',11,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=575',0,'revision','',0),(576,1,'2019-02-01 00:21:28','2019-02-01 00:21:28','<h3>To Our Clients</h3>\r\n<b>Working together to expand our horizons.</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-large wp-image-492\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/clients_gear-1024x464.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"238\" />Working with Moffitt International is working with intent. We at Moffitt understand the value of time, yours and ours. We will strive to insure that your experience with us will be the most pleasant and rewarding experience that you have had with an executive search and management consulting firm.\r\n\r\nOur consultants are both professional and specialized. Their years of experience coupled with specific industry focus allows them to provide you with the utmost attention and provide you with the potential candidates you need to reach your personal and firm goals.\r\n\r\nThe candidates that we develop on your behalf are typically not active in the marketplace. This allows us proper time for vetting and allows you a reasonable amount of time to ascertain the level of your investment you feel most comfortable. Candidates are a perishable commodity.\r\n<h3>Your Expectations of Us</h3>\r\nYour expectations of our firm include the following at a minimum. (Should you require anything in addition, please communicate those expectations clearly to us when appropriate).\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will treat your search or management consulting needs with the utmost discretion and confidentiality. We will not disclose your identity or specific engagement(s) until the appropriate time, depending on the circumstance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will respect your time. We will conduct ourselves within very strict industry ethical guidelines and will only present candidates or solutions that we feel are in your best interests. We will NOT make decisions at the (our) practice level that may affect you without your involvement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will communicate with you often. In the world of unified communications, we will strive to provide you updates across any number of platforms. However, you as the client may select the platform you most desire for that communication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will protect your interests. As professionals we understand the importance of our relationship. We strive through our process to protect your interests at all times. Your success is the paramount focus of our efforts. Whether your need is short term mission critical or part of a long term strategic plan, the outcome you desire will always be at the forefront of any effort we undertake on your behalf.</p>\r\n<h3>Our Expectations of You</h3>\r\nWithin the scope of your relationship with us, we have certain expectations of you. These expectations strictly have one goal in mind, mutual success. We are sensitive to how you desire to manage our search effort through the assignment</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">A</span>s a business to business consultancy, all of our fees are borne by you the client. Legal and regulatory consideration prevent us from charging or receiving consideration from individuals. We do not undertake any expenses without your specific request or permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"moffitt-body-button\" style=\"color: #445faa;\" href=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?page_id=15\">Get started</a>','Our Clients','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2019-02-01 00:21:28','2019-02-01 00:21:28','',11,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=576',0,'revision','',0),(577,1,'2019-02-01 00:22:34','2019-02-01 00:22:34','<h3>To Our Candidates</h3>\r\nWe believe that your experience with Moffitt will be the most satisfying and rewarding of any experience that you will have with an executive search and management consulting firm.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-large wp-image-437\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/candidates-1024x512.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"263\" />First and foremost, our consultants are professionals. This professionalism exhibits itself in our conduct, in our attention to detail and in our follow-up. We encourage you to get to really know your consultant. You will see the caliber of our professional who will be advising you in what is often one of the most important decisions you will ever make.\r\n\r\nSecondly, we represent some outstanding and dynamic clients. We thoroughly vet our clients to insure that your investment in time is worthwhile.\r\n\r\nLastly, you will receive excellent career counseling. Based on our interview with you and our reference checks, we will be able to give you an objective, third party analysis of your current career track and future possibilities. We will advise you of your strengths and also of areas which need improvement. Our motto, Hire. Integrity. means a great deal to our firm and our consultants. Making sure that you join the right organization at the right time is of paramount importance. You will find our counseling beneficial in your lifelong career progression.\r\n<h3>Your Expectations of Us</h3>\r\nOf course, there are certain expectations which candidates my have of Moffitt. These include the following:\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will treat your resume confidentially. It will not be sent to a client unless we have discussed the assignment with you. Most of our candidates are not actively on the market, however, they have chosen to be present in our files so that we may monitor their careers. Our confidentiality assures them that their current position will not be compromised.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will treat you with respect. Ninety-five percent of our serious candidates accept a job offer from our clients, which we believe says something about our ability to match clients and candidates. However, if you are made an offer and choose to decline, we will respect your decision. We may offer our viewpoint, but we will not attempt to make something happen that could ultimately fail. You may always be assured of our positive wished for you and your future. Your candidacy will remain intact for future assignments where we are engaged.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>e will communicate with you often. As we are advised of new information, we will offer you immediate feedback. In an error of unified communications, we ask that you take our calls and/or return our messages. Other forms of communication are too one dimensional to convey certain things. Additionally, you may also feel free to call us after business hours if necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">R</span>emember, there can only be one successful candidate for a position. If you are not selected as a candidate for one assignment, it will not impair your candidacy for others. In most cases, candidates are not selected because they are unqualified, there are simply other candidates that are better qualified. You may be disappointed, but the next assignment could be the better opportunity for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">A</span>s an employer paid firm, all of our fees and expenses are borne by our clients. There is never any fee or financial obligation on your part.</p>\r\n<h3>Our Expectations of You</h3>\r\nAt Moffitt, we have certain expectations of you, the Candidate, which must be met if the search process is to work effectively. These include the following:\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">W</span>henever you communicate with our client, call our consultant immediately and inform him or her of the conversation so that we may expedite the search process. Duplication of efforts can create confusion among the parties. As the professional(s) involved, the more timely the information, the more effective we can be.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">P</span>leave be honest with us as to any negative information about you personally and/or professionally that may or may not impact your career progression. This also applies to your overall management style within your current or previous organizations. If we are aware of these matters, we can review these with our client(s) at the beginning of the process to determine their relevancy, if any. However, if the negatives surface later, integrity rather than relevancy becomes the issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">Y</span>our travel expenses for interviews will be reimbursed to your directly by our clients. Please submit them to us for review. We will then forward the expense to the client for expedited reimbursement. Making us aware of said expenses will allow us to monitor their timely payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">R</span>emember that flexibility when interviewing is considered a positive attribute. Every effort will be made to accommodate your work schedule. You, our client(s) and our consultants are all very busy, so the more flexible your schedule the better.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"moffitt-accent-copy\"><span class=\"moffitt-accent-letter\">Y</span>our resume does not need to be perfect for our purposes. We do not require that you update your resume and prefer that you did not. We will interview you regarding your current employment and place that information into our professional format that represents you in the best manner.</p>\r\n\r\nTo learn more about how we search for candidates and our approach to our work, <a href=\"http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?page_id=15\">please contact us</a>.','Candidates','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-revision-v1','','','2019-02-01 00:22:34','2019-02-01 00:22:34','',13,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=577',0,'revision','',0),(578,1,'2019-02-01 00:26:32','2019-02-01 00:26:32','','moffitt_expertise','','inherit','closed','closed','','moffitt_expertise','','','2019-02-01 00:26:32','2019-02-01 00:26:32','',5,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/moffitt_expertise.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(579,1,'2019-02-01 00:26:47','2019-02-01 00:26:47','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','5-revision-v1','','','2019-02-01 00:26:47','2019-02-01 00:26:47','',5,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=579',0,'revision','',0),(580,0,'2019-02-01 00:55:47','2019-02-01 00:55:47','','','','publish','closed','closed','','580','','','2019-02-01 00:55:47','2019-02-01 00:55:47','',0,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?nf_sub=580',0,'nf_sub','',0),(582,1,'2019-01-30 16:30:41','2019-01-30 16:30:41','The Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) has identified 4 major categories of hazard that are the most responsible for the deaths of construction workers while on-the-clock.\r\n\r\nThese <a href=\"https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Fatal Four</a> were responsible for 59.9% of construction worker deaths in 2017. Out of 4,674 worker fatalities in private industry in 2017, twenty percent (or 971) were in construction. Stopping the so-called Fatal Four would theoretically save 582 lives every year in construction.\r\n\r\nOSHA, with its many partners, has had a considerable positive effect on workplace safety over the last four decades. Worker deaths in the U.S. are downon average from 38 worker deaths per day in 1970 to 14 a day in 2017.\r\n\r\nThis list of OSHAs Fatal Four shows the number of deaths in 2017 and the percentages in each category:\r\n\r\n1.<b>Falls</b>. 381 (39.2%)\r\n\r\n2.<b>Struck by Object</b>. 80 (8.2%)\r\n\r\n3.<b>Electrocutions</b>. 71 (7.3%)\r\n\r\n4.<b>Caught-In/Between</b>. 50 (5.1%)\r\n\r\nKendall Jones of ConstructConnect offers an overview of the four hazard categories and an in-depth discussion of each.\r\n\r\n<b>Fatal Four: Avoiding Constructions Deadliest Hazards</b>\r\n\r\nKendall Jones | ConstructConnect | March 9, 2016\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/blog-fatal-four-avoiding-constructions-deadliest-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/blog-fatal-four-avoiding-constructions-deadliest-hazards/</a>\r\n\r\n<i>Construction is one of the most dangerous industries to work in. One out of every five worker deaths last year was in construction, a percentage that has remained fairly constant over the last several years.</i>\r\n\r\nDetailed Analysis:<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-fall-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Falls</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-struck-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Struck by Object</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-electrocution-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Electrocutions</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-caught-inbetween-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Caught-In/Between</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<b>RELATED</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Fighting the Fatal Four: OSHA-Based Solutions to Constructions Deadliest Hazards</b>\r\n\r\nEllie Batchiyska | ConstructConnect | October 10, 2018\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/fighting-fatal-four-osha-based-solutions-constructions-deadliest-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/fighting-fatal-four-osha-based-solutions-constructions-deadliest-hazards/</a>\r\n\r\nAt first glance, the concept of the fatal four may sound like a scare tactic implemented by the Occupational Safety &amp; Health Administration (OSHA) to keep construction workers on their toes. However, these four hazards accounted for nearly 64% of construction worker deaths in 2016.\r\n\r\n<b>Construction\'s \"Fatal Four\"</b>\r\n\r\nOSHA Data &amp; Statistics / Commonly Used Statistics\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html</a>\r\n\r\nOut of 4,674 worker fatalities in private industry in calendar year 2017, 971 or 20.7% were in construction  that is, one in five worker deaths last year were in construction. The leading causes of private sector worker deaths (excluding highway collisions) in the construction industry were falls, followed by struck by object, electrocution, and caught-in/between.','OSHA\'s Fatal Four','','publish','closed','closed','','oshas-fatal-four','','','2019-02-01 17:00:22','2019-02-01 17:00:22','',0,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=582',0,'post','',0),(584,1,'2019-02-01 16:30:41','2019-02-01 16:30:41','The Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) has identified 4 major categories of hazard that are the most responsible for the deaths of construction workers while on-the-clock.\r\n\r\nThese <a href=\"https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Fatal Four</a> were responsible for 59.9% of construction worker deaths in 2017. Out of 4,674 worker fatalities in private industry in 2017, twenty percent (or 971) were in construction. Stopping the so-called Fatal Four would theoretically save 582 lives every year in construction.\r\n\r\nOSHA, with its many partners, has had a considerable positive effect on workplace safety over the last four decades. Worker deaths in the U.S. are downon average from 38 worker deaths per day in 1970 to 14 a day in 2017.\r\n\r\nThis list of OSHAs Fatal Four shows the number of deaths in 2017 and the percentages in each category:\r\n\r\n1.<b>Falls</b>. 381 (39.2%)\r\n\r\n2.<b>Struck by Object</b>. 80 (8.2%)\r\n\r\n3.<b>Electrocutions</b>. 71 (7.3%)\r\n\r\n4.<b>Caught-In/Between</b>. 50 (5.1%)\r\n\r\nKendall Jones of ConstructConnect offers an overview of the four hazard categories and an in-depth discussion of each.\r\n\r\n<b>Fatal Four: Avoiding Constructions Deadliest Hazards</b>\r\n\r\nKendall Jones | ConstructConnect | March 9, 2016\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/blog-fatal-four-avoiding-constructions-deadliest-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/blog-fatal-four-avoiding-constructions-deadliest-hazards/</a>\r\n\r\n<i>Construction is one of the most dangerous industries to work in. One out of every five worker deaths last year was in construction, a percentage that has remained fairly constant over the last several years.</i>\r\n\r\nDetailed Analysis:<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-fall-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Falls</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-struck-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Struck by Object</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-electrocution-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Electrocutions</a>|<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/construction-safety/avoiding-oshas-fatal-four-caught-inbetween-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Caught-In/Between</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<b>RELATED</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Fighting the Fatal Four: OSHA-Based Solutions to Constructions Deadliest Hazards</b>\r\n\r\nEllie Batchiyska | ConstructConnect | October 10, 2018\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/fighting-fatal-four-osha-based-solutions-constructions-deadliest-hazards/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.constructconnect.com/blog/fighting-fatal-four-osha-based-solutions-constructions-deadliest-hazards/</a>\r\n\r\nAt first glance, the concept of the fatal four may sound like a scare tactic implemented by the Occupational Safety &amp; Health Administration (OSHA) to keep construction workers on their toes. However, these four hazards accounted for nearly 64% of construction worker deaths in 2016.\r\n\r\n<b>Construction\'s \"Fatal Four\"</b>\r\n\r\nOSHA Data &amp; Statistics / Commonly Used Statistics\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">https://www.osha.gov/oshstats/commonstats.html</a>\r\n\r\nOut of 4,674 worker fatalities in private industry in calendar year 2017, 971 or 20.7% were in construction  that is, one in five worker deaths last year were in construction. The leading causes of private sector worker deaths (excluding highway collisions) in the construction industry were falls, followed by struck by object, electrocution, and caught-in/between.','OSHA\'s Fatal Four','','inherit','closed','closed','','582-revision-v1','','','2019-02-01 16:30:41','2019-02-01 16:30:41','',582,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/?p=584',0,'revision','',0),(585,1,'2019-02-01 16:45:38','2019-02-01 16:45:38','','blog_1','','inherit','closed','closed','','blog_1','','','2019-02-01 16:45:38','2019-02-01 16:45:38','',582,'http://localhost:8888/moffitt/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/blog_1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(586,1,'2019-01-29 17:06:51','2019-01-29 17:06:51','Relocating heavy construction equipment can be a major headache for contractorsand a major expense. It requires special care and expert planning to get the job done without damaging valuable equipment or violating local transport regulations.\r\n\r\nNow, experience and good planning can be supplemented by new technologies.<a href=\"https://www.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=6088254243889562846#editor/target=post;postID=5447722225644446622;onPublishedMenu=allposts;onClosedMenu=allposts;postNum=0;src=link\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">GenieBelt</a>tells us that incorporating smart technology into a project lik